# Git commits and attribution

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Made-with: Cursor`, or any Cursor/agent attribution to commits or PRs.
- Do not reference Cursor, AI assistants, or agents in commit messages, PR descriptions, code comments, documentation, or file headers.
- Use only the user's configured Git author name and email for commits.
- Write commit messages as short, professional, human-written summaries (imperative mood, no emojis, no "generated by" wording).
